chav1961.purelib.basic

Interface StackedFSM.StackedFSMCallback<Terminal extends Enum<?>,NonTerminal extends Enum<?>,Exit extends Enum<?>,Stack,Parameter>

  • Type Parameters:
    Terminal - terminal (in the terms of FSM)
    NonTerminal - non-terminal (in the terms of FSM)
    Exit - exit symbol (in the terms of FSM)
    Stack - stack content type (in the terms of FSM)
    Parameter - any cargo to pass thru the FSM to FSM callback
    Enclosing class:
    StackedFSM<Terminal extends Enum<?>,NonTerminal extends Enum<?>,Stack,Exit extends Enum<?>,Parameter>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface StackedFSM.StackedFSMCallback<Terminal extends Enum<?>,NonTerminal extends Enum<?>,Exit extends Enum<?>,Stack,Parameter>

    This interface describes a callback to process successful stacked FSM state changes.

    Since:
    0.0.2
    Author:
    Alexander Chernomyrdin aka chav1961

       throws FlowException

        Process callback of the FSM

        Parameters:
        fsm - fsm instance that calls this method
        terminal - terminal from the FSM.processTerminal(Enum, Object) method
        fromState - current state of the FSM
        top - top of the stack
        toState - new state of the FSM
        stack - action to make with the stack
        action - action list for the given state jump
        parameter - parameter from the FSM.processTerminal(Enum, Object) method
        Returns:
        stack value to push into stack if the stack action is StackedFSM.StackAction.PUSH
        Throws:
        FlowException - indicate any processing errors
